text: Gossens was a municipality in Yverdon in the canton of Vaud in Switzerland. It became part of neighbouring Donneloye on 1 January 2008.Amtliches Gemeindeverzeichnis der Schweiz published by the Swiss Federal Statistical Office accessed 19 July 2011 It is on the main road between Yverdon and Moudon. The economy is mostly agricultural. == References == ==Other websites== Category:2008 disestablishments in Switzerland Category:Former municipalities of Vaud Category:Villages in Vaud
